was interrupted by the hurried beat of a drum, and soon everything died down, and in place of the puffed-out sounds of trumpets there came again the imperturbable clopping of hoofs and the subdued rattling of a St. Petersburg morning.

'You forget to put out the light in the corridor,' said smiling, his landlady, an elderly German woman. 'You forget to close your door at night.' And she also complained to his fiancée — saying he was absentminded like an old professor.

